.TH TO7ASCII 1 "November 11, 2025" "" "User commands"
.SH NAME \"{{{roff}}}\"{{{
to7ascii \- Microsoft Basic for 8-bit Thomson T07/M05/T07-70 program files detokenizer 
.\"}}}
.SH SYNOPSIS \"{{{
.ad l
.B to7ascii < tokenized.bas > listing.txt
.ad b
.\"}}}
.SH DESCRIPTION \"{{{
.SS "Introduction" \"{{{
.B to7ascii
is a detokenizer for Microsoft Basic for Thomson TO7/MO5/TO7-70 program
files. Thomson 8-bit
microcomputers were built around Motorola 6809 microprocessors and
were used in French middle and high schools in the 1980s following
the \fI Informatique pour Tous \fR plan of 1985. To save space in
computer memory and on tapes or floppy disks, the Basic keywords were 
replaced by single byte or two-byte tokens. \fBto7ascii\fP reads 
on stanfard input a  Basic file saved in tokenized format and outputs  
the Basic program in ASCII format on standard output. The program may then
be used with a Unix traditional Basic interpreter such as
\fBbwbasic(1)\fP,\fPbas(1)\fP or \fBblassic(1)\fP. 
.\"}}}

